		<div class="concept-text">
			<h4 style="color: var(--violet)">Tool, instrument, agent: a spectrum</h4>
			<p>The Kim et al. paper inherits a long-running argument from NIME and HCI: an AI music system can sit anywhere on a continuum between <em>tool</em> (every output is explicitly chosen by the musician), <em>instrument</em> (the musician shapes behavior through performance, but the system contributes choices within its learned model), and <em>agent</em> (the system perceives context and adapts strategy mid-performance). Most current systems live ambiguously between tool and instrument, and almost none cleanly clear the bar for "agent" in the AI sense. The label a designer picks for their own system constrains the questions they ask about it.</p>
		</div>
	</div>

