		<div class="concept-text">
			<h4 style="color: var(--orange)">Aesthetic expectations are inputs</h4>
			<p>The Pelinski paper's central move is to argue that the cultural narratives we hold about AI music (what it should sound like, what it conjures up, who it's haunted by) actively shape the design choices we make. These narratives aren't retrospective descriptions of what the technology produced; they're upstream constraints we keep applying to the technology. The example in the paper is their own: while developing <em>Surfing Hyperparameters</em>, the team kept narrating their system's outputs in ways that confirmed expectations they'd held since the start. "Sounding like AI" wasn't an emergent property of the system. It was the brief.</p>
		</div>
	</div>

