		<div class="concept-text">
			<h4 style="color: var(--teal)">A design space, not a leaderboard</h4>
			<p>Most AI-music papers compare systems on a small set of metrics and pick a winner. The Kim et al. paper deliberately doesn't do that. The point of a design space is that there's no single "best" location in it; different cells make sense for different performers, contexts, and traditions. By plotting 184 systems across several axes (musical input, agent capability, interaction modality, output representation, alongside contextual axes like usage and ecosystem), the authors show <em>where</em> systems cluster and <em>where</em> the empty regions are. The empty regions are part of the contribution.</p>
		</div>
	</div>

